										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><br>In French, my&nbsp;last name, <em>duChemin</em>, means &#8220;of the road.&#8221; I was born to travel. I got my first passport just six&nbsp;weeks after I was born, and took my first international flight when I was six&nbsp;months old. I&#8217;ve now photographed in 59 countries and all seven continents. It&#8217;s fair to say I&#8217;ve packed a lot of bags and have some strong opinions about the gear I choose to travel with.<br></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="2400" height="1600" src="https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_10215.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-21244" srcset="https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_10215.jpg 2400w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_10215-150x100.jpg 150w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_10215-500x333.jpg 500w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_10215-768x512.jpg 768w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_10215-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_10215-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_10215-100x67.jpg 100w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_10215-864x576.jpg 864w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_10215-1200x800.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 2400px) 100vw, 2400px" /></figure>



<p><br>For the last 15 years,&nbsp;<a href="https://guragear.com/?ref=tezywyhs" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Gura Gear </a>has been with me on every trip. I use their Kiboko 30L camera bags, the Chobe&nbsp;computer satchel,&nbsp;and now their Mara duffel bags. In every one of those bags, you&#8217;ll find their various EtCetera accessory pouches keeping me organized. I love the design, rely on the quality, and am so proud and grateful to have Gura Gear support my work. And, though you shouldn&#8217;t need it, its customer support is second to none.</p>



<p>So late last year, they reached out and asked,&nbsp;&#8220;Can we send you anything?&#8221;&nbsp;I looked around my office at all the piles of gear and the bags those piles would&nbsp;go in and, probably for the first time ever, thought, &#8220;Wow—there&#8217;s nothing I need.&#8221; I didn&#8217;t even recognize myself as I said it.</p>



<p>But then I thought of you and asked if they&#8217;d be willing to share that same love with&nbsp;you. It wasn&#8217;t just an immediate yes;&nbsp;they said, &#8220;Send us a list.&#8221; So I did, and not only did they give me everything on that&nbsp;list, they added to it. And together, we&#8217;re giving it all away.<br></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="2400" height="1601" src="https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20230910-duChemin-Peter-Holst-Headshots-279.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-21245" srcset="https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20230910-duChemin-Peter-Holst-Headshots-279.jpg 2400w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20230910-duChemin-Peter-Holst-Headshots-279-150x100.jpg 150w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20230910-duChemin-Peter-Holst-Headshots-279-500x334.jpg 500w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20230910-duChemin-Peter-Holst-Headshots-279-768x512.jpg 768w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20230910-duChemin-Peter-Holst-Headshots-279-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20230910-duChemin-Peter-Holst-Headshots-279-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20230910-duChemin-Peter-Holst-Headshots-279-100x67.jpg 100w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20230910-duChemin-Peter-Holst-Headshots-279-864x576.jpg 864w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20230910-duChemin-Peter-Holst-Headshots-279-1200x801.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 2400px) 100vw, 2400px" /></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><br><strong>Gura Gear is giving us three&nbsp;great prizes, and all you have to do is leave a comment here on my blog (below) by February 07&nbsp;to enter. We&#8217;ll then do a random draw on February 08 and select three&nbsp;names for the following&nbsp;prizes:</strong></h4>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>First prize is a Kiboko 30L+ Camera Backpack (black)</strong>. WINNER: Alison Bowditch</h4>



<p><a href="https://guragear.com/collections/camera-backpacks/products/kiboko-30l-camera-backpack-with-laptop-sleeve?ref=tezywyhs" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">This is the same bag I&#8217;ve travelled the world with for the last 15+ years</a>, though it&#8217;s been updated with a laptop sleeve. This bag is one of the lightest on the market, fits into every plane I&#8217;ve ever been on except the smallest regional jets, but that&#8217;s not fair because <em>nothing</em>&nbsp;much bigger than a laptop fits into those overhead bins, though even then it will fit under the seat. It&#8217;s also one of the few bags that will take a 600/4.0 lens. The design is exceptional, and the build quality is brilliant. I&#8217;ve carried this bag comfortably through too many airports to count, and it has never let me down.<br><br>How much do I love this bag? I have eight&nbsp;of them in all different sizes and&nbsp;colours. Don&#8217;t judge me; I like my camera bags, and I&#8217;m a weak man.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="2400" height="1600" src="https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_11620-1.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-21246" srcset="https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_11620-1.jpg 2400w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_11620-1-150x100.jpg 150w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_11620-1-500x333.jpg 500w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_11620-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_11620-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_11620-1-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_11620-1-100x67.jpg 100w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_11620-1-864x576.jpg 864w, https://d3c0aoh0dus5lw.cloudfront.net/WP/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/20251020_David-Duchemin_11620-1-1200x800.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 2400px) 100vw, 2400px" /></figure>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Me and my Mara 60L Duffel. Dressing to match is entirely optional.&nbsp;</em></p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Second prize is a 60L Mara Duffel Bag (Sahara)</strong>. WINNER: Aaron Carpenter</h4>



<p><a href="https://guragear.com/products/mara-travel-duffel?ref=tezywyhs&amp;variant=45614976467197" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">This is the same bag I&#8217;ve&nbsp;packed for next month&#8217;s month-long&nbsp;trip to Kenya.</a> Made from the same X-pac fabric used for their camera bags, it&#8217;s the lightest and most durable fabric available. I can put a lot of stuff into this bag, and the internal pockets help keep it organized. With great grab handles&nbsp;and comfortable backpack straps (if you want them), this duffle is my new favourite.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Third prize is an accessories package.</strong> WINNER: Troy Patterson</h4>



<p>Three EtCetera pouches (one <a href="https://guragear.com/collections/camera-supports/products/et-cetera-pouch-medium-1?ref=tezywyhs" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">medium</a>, one <a href="https://guragear.com/collections/camera-supports/products/et-cetera-case-s-1?ref=tezywyhs" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">small</a>, one <a href="https://guragear.com/collections/camera-supports/products/et-cetera-case-xs-1?ref=tezywyhs" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">x-small</a>), a <a href="https://guragear.com/collections/camera-supports/products/tembo-12-memory-card-wallet?ref=tezywyhs" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Tembo card wallet</a>, and one of their brand new tech organizers (so new I&#8217;m not sure it&#8217;s even on the website yet). If you keep saying you&#8217;re finally going to get all those little bits and pieces organized, this will help. My bags and Pelican cases are full of the EtCetera pouches—they&#8217;re the only way I can keep track of all the smaller bits of gear, the batteries, the chargers and cables, etc.  This package is worth about USD$150.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>That&#8217;s almost $1,000 worth of some of the best kit I&#8217;ve ever used, and GuraGear is just giving it away, no strings attached. All you have to do is leave a comment on my blog. How easy is&nbsp;<em>that?</em></strong></h4>



<p>Just keep scrolling to the comments and tell me you&#8217;re in. Say &#8220;Pick me!&#8221; or &#8220;Thank you&#8221; or &#8220;I like bears.&#8221; It doesn&#8217;t matter what you say; just tell me you want your name in the draw. Want bonus points? You could make sure you&#8217;re following <a href="https://www.instagram.com/gura.gear/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">@gura.gear</a> and me (<a href="https://www.instagram.com/davidduchemin/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">@davidduchemin</a>) on Instagram. It won&#8217;t increase your chance of winning, but we&#8217;d feel the love, and you can&#8217;t have too much love these days.</p>



<p>I use every one of these bags and pouches almost every day that I&#8217;m working and travelling. My relationship with <a href="https://guragear.com/?ref=tezywyhs" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Gura Gear</a> is a long one, and I&#8217;ve bought most of these bags with my own money because they&#8217;re worth every penny. But I&#8217;m excited for some of you to get your hands on them. I&#8217;ll do the draw on February 07 and announce the&nbsp;winners with an update to this post here on my blog on February 08.<br><br>Good Luck!<br><br>For the Love of the Photograph,<br>David</p>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<p><strong>GIVEAWAY WINNERS:</strong></p>



